subSubSection.paragraph:
Mesosoma (
Fig. 17
): Mesonotum sparsely covered with long erect setae; mesoscutum smooth, with deep median sulcus; anterior surface forming lateral carina; anterior margin not excavated; dorsal surface flat in lateral view; short depression of parapsides present but indistinct; lateral lobe absent; axilla smooth, flat, separated medially (
Fig. 17
); scuto-scutellar sulcus forming deep continuous groove; scutellum smooth, weakly rounded; ventral part of mesepisternum bearing sparsely located setae; metanotum densely covered with minute punctures, hairy; propodeum with paired longitudinal median, submedian and lateral carinae; carinae parallel, rarely slightly diverging anteriorly; surface between longitudinal carinae transversely rugose; posterior margin of median region not produced; posterior transversal carina absent.

Forewing (
Fig. 16
) hyaline; vein M 1.62.3 × basal part of RS.

(Male) Different from female as follows: body sometimes densely covered by small punctures (
Figs 21, 22
): distance between punctures as long as diameter of puncture; elevation of vertex less developed in smaller specimens; antenna entirely testaceous to brown; head and mesosoma sometimes reddish brown (
Figs 20–23
) with median mesoscutal sulcus, scuto-scutellar sulcus and propodeum black; sometimes body entirely testaceous.
